,Not Recommended,238240,26205108,"Posted: 24 October, 2016",all,Nanostrike,"THIS GAME IS AN EARLY ACCESS SCAMDevelopers realized their game wasn't working out and had too many issues to fix.  But instead of telling their customers this, they rushed to a ""Full Release"" version that was hilariously unfinished in September 2015 so they could get the game featured on the Steam Store Front Page right before the holidays.They strung it along further by releasing constant ""Minor updates"" up through December 2015.  These updates weren't actually intended to fix their horribly broken game, but intended to keep it showing on the Steam Store Front Page as ""Recently Updated"" throughout the 2015 holiday season.In January 2016, by all appearances, this developer had stopped all development.  The community manager had left, they were inactive on Social Media and Steam, and nothing was done to fix the games issues.In April 2016, they posted a vague ""Please be patient"" message on Steam via a private steam account (Which, to this day, doesn't respond to inquiries about the game).  By ""Coincidence"", one month later, in May 2016, the game is featured in a Humble Indie Bundle.  The April Post was done simply to make potential Humble Bundle buyers believe that the game is being actively developed and supported were they to check it's news page.  The devs apparently had no intention of continuing work on the game, they just wanted to string folks along and milk every last dime they could from sales, even from within the Humble Bundle.Their website and forums were taken down after the domain names are currently up for sale.  None of their social media accounts (Facebook, Twitter, ect) have posted anything or responded to anything.  E-Mails are unanswered.  No new activity on Steam.This is a classic ""Take the money and run"" Early-Access scam, on par with what the developers of Towns did.  This needs to stop.  DO NOT buy this game.  If you do, you support these practices.  I bought into the game in it's Early Alpha stages and regret doing so.  Spread the word about developers like this and be more discerning in the future about your Early Access Purchases.  That's the only way this kinda crap is going to stop."
