,Recommended,238240,15715281,"Posted: 6 May, 2015",all,Ersatz Soul,"I've bought this game when it was v0.16 or something and played around many versions and at time i write this review i have like 200h played.To keep it short - i like this game pretty much and game quite improved since long ago. Shamefully, no longer supported.To tell the truth, 1.0`s feature wasnt suprise for me since i was in inner test team, yet those changes from last public build to 1.0 made game much more and quite much more entertaining. I'd even say it made game lively - tons of different events waiting for you to blow up (well, some of them do require you to bomb some places).So, what's this game about? - it's about exploration of planet, on which you had emergency landing when ArkCo`s shop crashed (watch the intro cinematics for more story) - thus you're alone (or not - if multiplayer with friends) and now you need to explore this world, getting resources and making better  equipment in process (typical for all such games). Further you go down - better resources, more dungerous enemies, new places to visit. For most actions you get XP to spend in knowledge window to get access to better gear and new facilities.EoS is about exploring ONE planet (different each time you make new world, following some generation rules obviously), furthermore - exploring it VERTICALLY - there are 3 biomes, which is placed vertically, even thought you will explore it in rather horisontal line, then moving down to next one. Also, note there isnt any solid terrain - rather flying chunks of it (codex it for why), thus you will not be forced to dig through solid terrain to get lower and lower.Many ppl complaining about game being too hardcore at start since weapon you begin with sucks at dmg (lol, ppl didnt even bother opening crafting window to see 1 scematics of better gun being avaible). But dont get too relaxed - most of things on this planet seems to be made to be human-killers and death can me quick and/or painful :3Ii expect ppl crying in few days about dying and respawning at start as annoying feature - even thought u can make and bind urself to better cryopods (respawn facility) to get respawn-at-dying-place points on time bases - cryorods.Btw - game has no tutorial, outside window with knowledge - CODEX - about thing you find/unlocked and flying laser shark, which will teach you some basics. Why? - well, for world's optimisation and....more hilariously, some ppl failed to finish tutorial or even simply passed by w/o learning and then stormed forum/reviews with questions tutorial had answer on :3Really, so far it's not very hard to understand a game.Those confused by low % of positive rewievs - most of negatives are made by those, who didnt bother to lurking around about game or didnt play enough (under 10hours - not even worth looking at), as well as people wanting Starbound clone.For more detailed comparison of EoS/Starbound/Terraria/etc visithttp://steamcommunity.com/app/238240/discussions/0/540735426074163826/Pros:- interactions with developers - they do respond within a day (depending on timeline of yours) and they're friendly. Seriously, they even used to run server to play with players and they do take in account suggestions of players about what to implement;- helpful people;- Quite big sandbox-generated world - can travel to new places, see alot monsters and kill them. 3 biomes with different flora, fauna - so you will not see all the same things for whole game.- build your base, place facilities and decorate at your taste (alot stuff will be coming, thought even now you can spend few hours decorating);- rpg-oriented - alot stuff to research, player-style-oriented armor sets and kits;- quite nice amount of armors (3 trees: fighter, explorer, builder - all with unique and useful bonuses), weapons (phase - unlimited ammo and weak strikes, projectiles - limited powerful crafted ammo, energy - not present yet) and facilities to place;- SCI-FI setting;- some humorous moments;- Pretty nice graphics;Cons:- only English as supported language atm;- no way to pause game (thought placing command node and teleporting to command center placed in your haven saves the day);- a bit hard to set multiplayer server - there is a complete How-To guide on forum thought;- not exatly your average YOBA in terms of game's info - well, Codex, npcs and your brain should be enough to figure out the game (at least many questions are answered on forum since long ago)neutral:- farming - as in any rpg of such type, you gonna need to get resources for ur stuff, thpught getting most of resources isnt hard during traveling - just keep your eyes open. If playing solo - one might consider getting builder sets for quicker digging;- 2d game - yep, no realistic 3D graphics (like in 60-usd games);- not newbie-friendly in some terms (tutorial thing explained above), since not everything is explained, chewed for you and put in your mouth with spoon. If you run into trouble - i'm currently making game's guide:http://steamcommunity.com//sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=448294464feel free to open it. If reading forum and guide still left you with question - feel free to ask me.- more multiplayer-oriented, than singleplayer game (noone stops from playing alone thought. Truth to be told, i donno about other simular games and their MP/SP orientation)state of game:- 3 biomes present and filled (with mobs, plants, events and stuff).- dungeons - instances to find some specific resources and bosses.- animal mounts and vehicles;- multiplayer (thought require to have someone hosting server);- guns (3 trees) and melee, armors (3 different trees w different type of bonuses), upgrades, facilities and stuff in quite nice amounts;- NPCs - somewhat funny bunch;- terrafroming is present))- achievements.- trading cards :3"
