76561198047021954,Not Recommended,238240,21018009,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Hak,Runs like a wellsprings camp escapee.
,Recommended,238240,11969020,"Posted: 3 September, 2014",all,Asvarduil,"""Edge of Space"" is a construction/adventure game in the vein of Terraria, only in space!  It's a very simple premise, but somehow, as of this writing, the game doesn't quite deliver on either its potential or the intellectual legacy of Terraria, which great effort is put into establishing.The first thing to realize about this game is that there are some really cool ideas!  You've got a laser drill, and you start with projectile weapons!.  The graphics are a miss for me (I'll get into why later), but are certainly more detailed than Terraria's, and may not be as offensive to another gamer's eye.(The following edited as of 21 May 2015...)The game has vastly improved since my playthrough last year!  The general user experience is far less irritating than it was, and actually warrants my giving this game a chance now.What WorksThe game's crafting system is awesome.  Pretty much, the game is already similar to the ""Terraria Leveled"" mod in some ways mechanically, but the research lines are well-defined, and the experience amounts required to unlock a tier feel correct.  What's more the amount of things you can craft without a crafting station is great for upgrading your field arsenal (from what I've seen so far.)They fixed the guns to always hit.  This wasthedealbreaker for me before.  Thank you.  Note to other game developers: in an action game, RNG-based miss mechanics arevery very bad.  What's more the base tier of stuff after completing the tutorial isactually useful, which is nice!Speaking of the tutorial, it appears simplified from the version I played earlier, and is effective at basically teaching the game.  Less was indeed more!You can rebind keys.  This helps to mitigate some of the confusing keybindings in this game, and let you play Your Way™.What Doesn't WorkFirst, you still spawn on a sky island instead of the planet's surface.  I think this is a mistake, even with jetpacks being available immediately, because jumping into a void beneath your little sky island is too much of an early risk, that I don't think a new player wants to take - at this point, we're still getting a feel for the game and the world.Second - re-evaluate your default key bindings.  V for crafting and C for character are really counterintuitive to me.  While providing rebindable keys is nice, nailing a good preset will help this game immensely.  It was irritating to have to click the menu button every time I wanted to craft something, until I found the hotkey.Speaking of crafting, the way you spend XP feelsincrediblyclunky, and the increment/decrement textfield used to implement it clashes with everything else.  Since the upgrades are straight lines, not trees, why not just allow me to click an upgrade or a button on the upgrade in order to ""buy"" it with the XP?The visual style to me is hit or miss, but this gets into personal preference; if Terraria is a Saturday-morning cartoon, then this isArcheron Adult Swim, which is what I think they're going for.  This point may or may not be a sticking point for you; this ""Doesn't Work"" bit is purely subjective.  Some sprite mods or the ability to create sprite/tile image mods might be a good idea, though.The (New) TL;DROnce, I did not recommend this game; it wasn't ready for the public.  Luckily a few patches seem to have come and gone to help resolve that situation.  The developers need to study up on good User Experience (UX) quite a bit more, and take it as a lesson learned going forward - UX seems to be one of their weaknesses that they have to fight against.  However, the interesting ideas in this game seem significantly closer to fruition.I recommend watching this title more closely..."
