,Not Recommended,238240,9578922,"Posted: 20 March, 2014",all,supernet2,"Im giving this game a maybe for playing. Theirs barely any difference from this vs terraria. Oh wait their is, just a radiation exposure bar, and the game seems to be styled around metroid graphics.Onto the real review. Okay basically your use to terraria, starbound, or minecraft. You assume you have the basics of building, thats check.Now you assume you have the basics of base building, that is... barely check. You have a command center, but your given no real idea how it works, or how to use it. 0 Explanation behind it. (HINT) it supplies 2 available slots for structures that require power (Which AGAIN are not defined, nor explained) how to mine or make adjacent to a powered block (and to do that you need to mine the back, currently the mining in the background has been switched to TAB key).Anyway... now assume after base building is scrapped, most of what you seen in the pictures, or the trailer video is either not implemented yet or considered non user useable. Thats... thats just false advertising. DO NOT BUY THIS GAME based on the trailier. You will be SEVERELY disappointed if you do!Anyway, other than this review just remember... with a grain of salt.  Comparing this game to minecraft is laughable at best, as minecraft is one of the most fleshed out, well prepared games out their for survival. Just its block based graphics.With Starbound you get the perks of it having terraria gameplay with a twist, mechs, turrets, space ship home & planetary home combine with world travelining leading to finte adventures.With Terraria you get alota building functionality but... only one world, on the upside in Terraria you also get to transfer items on your character with you to other servers.With this game Edge of Space you... get working building mechanics (barely anything to craft though), good music (when its not tearing horribly or desyncing), horribly slow mining, extremely aggressive enemy npcs that fight you based on how far down you go, and how pre-occupied you are not paying attention to your surroundings, and limited idea of how to really play altogether with out continued communication through the steam forums with other players, and the developer(s)/staff of Edge of Space.If you want this game buy it, i bought 2 copies, but now im beginning to regret my investment considering how much is lacking, how much is currently missing, and what is functional, works, and what isnt combine with all the time lost to just... well... mining, searching, and trying to figure out this game altogether with searching the steam forums, and trial and error in the game itself. Anyway good luck!Oh and so far it runs for me on a Asus Transformer T100 series (1.83ghz quad core, 2gb ram) with 15minutes load time, and on low/normal graphics (on my other laptops/desktops) the game runs at normal/high. Lag doesn't seem to be existant in any gameplay on this game on any of the computers i've tested it with (all being at 1.83ghz, 4.2ghz, or 3.9ghz quad core) computing systems.*Note*Still consider this game and check back on it though! It does show promise assuming alot of the negatives i've listed, not including thousands of other negatives listed in the forums are taken care of."
