,Not Recommended,238240,10969229,"Posted: 30 June, 2014",all,Leonassan {CEWR},"After speaking with LadyAijou extensively regarding Edge of Space. I would like to update my review with some further information.The reason advancement isn't working is right before the steam summer sale most of the NPC code was gutted out for revamping, very similar to what Rust is doing. The team at Handyman Studios was not expecting to get featured in the flash sale and ended up receiving more orders during that eight hour period than they had gotten in their previous best week during the 2-1 sale.The development team consists of two people, one of which had a system failure right after the change to the NPC code was implemented, which meant that what should have been fixed either right before or right after the flash sale was unable to be fixed. The chests dropping from nests is related to this issue because the nest/event has to spawn the appropriate creatures and then track that they have been killed, which with the changes to the NPC code is not working properly, so you're ""failing"" every nest/event you start.This means that yes, at this particular moment it is not possible to progress past the first biome. With full aluminum armor you can make it pretty much to the end of the first biome, but beyond that is not possible. I will be leaving my review as ""not recommended"" for the time being due to the non-available features, but will hold my final opinion in reserve until such time as the current mess is cleaned up."
